		<descript>
			<langdata>eng</langdata>
			<abstract>Beijing Orthoimagery is a set of digital orthophotos representing Beijing, China.. The dataset is comprised of nine tiles; the photos were taken in 2005 and 2006 and have a 60 centimeter resolution.</abstract>
			<purpose>Orthophotos serve a variety of purposes for both display and analysis. This dataset is for non-commercial research purposes only.</purpose>
			<supplinf>This dataset is available via the ArcSDE from the EDS lab via this .lyr file:
https://www1.columbia.edu/sec/acis/eds/dgate/studies/C1301/data/landinfo_beijing_imagery_2007.zip</supplinf>
		</descript>
